{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:45:55.784130+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 13f692f414ab9fb9bc397b72a6c13de9db1c8cb6)", "id": "lc_911c0a48-df34-46be-a3f9-a88ce90a55fa"}, {"type": "text", "text": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n  <head>\n    <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n    <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no\">\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"<%- description %>\">\n    <link rel=\"icon\" href=\"/favicon.ico\">\n    <title><%- title %></title>\n  </head>\n  <body>\n    <noscript>\n      <strong>We're sorry but <%- title %> doesn't work properly without JavaScript enabled. Please enable it to continue.</strong>\n    </noscript>\n    <div id=\"app\"></div>\n    <script type=\"module\" src=\"/src/main.js\"></script>\n  </body>\n</html>", "id": "lc_3d60f7b0-ae02-464d-a16e-e652c8e23a9f"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "b4496b61-8a75-4c47-9b9c-13d3bfd46e68", "tool_call_id": "call_fd63267d92cd46669f4dd73b", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T23:46:16.764406+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## App Bootstrap, Routing, and Layout Rendering\n\n### 1. Entry Point — `index.html`\n\nThe browser loads `index.html`, which contains a single mount point `<div id=\"app\"></div>` and a module script tag pointing to `/src/main.js`.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Bootstrap — `src/main.js`\n\n```js\nimport { createPinia } from 'pinia'\nimport { createApp } from 'vue'\nimport Default from '@/layouts/default/Default.vue'\nimport App from './App.vue'\nimport { router } from './router'\n\nconst app = createApp(App)\n\napp.component('LayoutDefault', Default)   // global layout component\napp.use(createPinia())                     // state management\napp.use(router)                            // vue-router\n\napp.mount('#app')\n```\n\nThree things happen here:\n\n1. **The Vue app is created** from the root component `App.vue`.\n2. **The default layout** (`Default.vue`) is registered as a **global component** named `LayoutDefault`, making it available everywhere without explicit imports.\n3. **Pinia** (store) and **Vue Router** are installed as plugins. The app is then mounted to `#app`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Layout Selection — `src/App.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <component :is=\"layout\">\n    <RouterView />\n  </component>\n</template>\n\n<script>\nimport '@/scss/app.scss'\n\nexport default {\n  name: 'App',\n  computed: {\n    layout() {\n      return `layout-${this.$route.meta.layout || 'default'}`\n    },\n  },\n}\n</script>\n```\n\n`App.vue` is the shell of every page. It uses Vue's dynamic `<component :is=\"...\">` to resolve the layout at runtime:\n\n- It reads `this.$route.meta.layout` from the current route.\n- If no layout is specified in `meta`, it falls back to `'default'`.\n- The resolved string (e.g. `\"layout-default\"`) matches the globally registered component `LayoutDefault`.\n\nThe child `<RouterView />` is rendered **inside** that layout component via its default `<slot>`.\n\n---\n\n### 4. The Default Layout — `src/layouts/default/Default.vue`\n\n```vue\n<template>\n  <div class=\"default-page-wrapper\">\n    <DefaultNav />\n    <slot />\n    <DefaultFooter />\n  </div>\n</template>\n```\n\nThis layout provides the persistent chrome (navigation bar + footer) and exposes a `<slot />` where the routed view component is injected. It also applies sticky-footer styling.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Routing Configuration — `src/router/index.js`\n\n```js\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: '/',\n    name: 'Home',\n    component: Home,                        // eagerly loaded\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n  {\n    path: '/about',\n    name: 'About',\n    component: () => import(/* webpackChunkName: \"about\" */ '../views/About.vue'), // lazy-loaded\n    meta: { layout: 'default' },\n  },\n]\n```\n\n- **Hash-based history** (`createWebHashHistory`) is used, so URLs look like `/#/about`.\n- The `Home` route eagerly imports `Home.vue`.\n- The `About` route uses **dynamic `import()`** (route-level code-splitting).\n\n---\n\n### 6. How the About Page Loads (Step by Step)\n\n1. **User navigates to `/#/about`** (or clicks a router-link to `/about`).\n2. **Vue Router** matches the `/about` route entry. Because the component is a dynamic import returning a `Promise`, the chunk `about.[hash].js` is **fetched on demand** from the server.\n3. While the chunk loads, the route is not yet active (the router's `beforeRouteEnter` guard is pending).\n4. Once the chunk arrives, `About.vue` is resolved:\n\n   ```vue\n   <template>\n     <div class=\"container\">\n       <h1>This is the about page</h1>\n     </div>\n   </template>\n   ```\n\n5. The router activates the `/about` route, setting `this.$route.meta.layout` to `'default'`.\n6. `App.vue`'s computed `layout` resolves to `\"layout-default\"`, which maps to the globally registered `LayoutDefault` component.\n7. `Default.vue` renders: `DefaultNav` → **`<slot>` filled with `About.vue`** → `DefaultFooter`.\n\n**Key takeaway:** The About page is **code-split** and lazy-loaded only when the user navigates to `/about`, while the layout shell (nav + footer) is already present and reused thanks to the global component registration pattern.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 1033, "prompt_tokens": 8618, "total_tokens": 9651, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 38, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 8128, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0011411208, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002424108, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00089871}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780962356-jQC1JOgKLNT5GL214RWc", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9a0-ea49-70c0-978e-123b06f6e91c-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 8618, "output_tokens": 1033, "total_tokens": 9651, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 8128}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 38}}}}]}}}
